summary: I believe in the pursuit of knowledge, self education, will power, self discipline, and honing all aspects of my physical and mental health.I'm a college dropout, now a software engineer. I was studying English, and decided a lifetime of working in the food service industry wasn't what I wanted. So I cracked books, Good Will Hunting style, and here I am now. How do you like them apples? #NoStudentLoansI think the biggest mistake I ever made was thinking I absolutely needed a degree. If this statement bothers you, kindly move on.I spend a lot of time in the gym, and I'm also into cooking food (and eating it), going hiking, taking dance classes, working, reading books, and listening to audiobooks. I tend to love everything I do and I'm never bored.Personal growth and ambition are both important to me. This decade, my thirties, is dedicated to both of those, as well as gratitude, mindfulness, professional development, and physical fitness.I've heard that there are only two problems: 1) you know what you want but you don't know how to get it, and 2) you don't know what you want.I know what I want.
